The paper deals with the satisfiability problem for regular grammar logics with converse, which is a topic in logic and automated reasoning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science). However, the paper also discusses the translation of modal logics into first-order logic, which is relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and formal language theory (cs.FL). Additionally, the use of GF2, which is a fragment of first-order logic, suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-categories of data structures (cs.DS) and programming languages (cs.PL).
